    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName>Ipswich</placeName>
                        <date>6 June 1851</date>
                        <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>I did not return you my thanks for the letter &amp; the printed notice of your excellent plan of Geological Chronology as exemplified in the Museum at Ipswich. Pray accept them now. I wish to ask if you know enough of Mr Searles Wood (who on account of his Crag papers must all praise) to judge if it would be a suitable thing to ask him to be one of the Secretaries to the Section of Geology?</p>
                        <p>We shall ask you (I believe) to add to your other duties these:</p>
                        <p>to preside in Section D,</p>
                        <p>to preside one day at the ordinary perhaps the earliest, on Wednesday July 2.-</p>
                        <p>Ever Yours truly</p>
                        <p>John Phillips</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
